    A generic persistent immutable Set implementation, with three types of methods:
    1. Read methods from Set, such as contains(java.lang.Object)
    2. Write methods from Set, such as add(T); these will throw UnsupportedOperationException
      3. and have been marked as @Deprecated
    3. Persistent "modification" methods, such as with(T); these will efficiently create modified copies of the current set
